<section>
  <h2>Easiest way to&nbsp;deploy</h2>
  <p>Upstatic makes deploying to <a href="http://aws.amazon.com/s3/" rel="external">Amazon&nbsp;S3</a> as easy as pushing changes to GitHub. It automatically creates S3&nbsp;bucket and configures that for website hosting—all&nbsp;you&nbsp;need is Amazon&nbsp;credentials.</p>
  <pre id="terminal"><code>upstatic deploy<i class="cursor"></i></code>
<span class="progress"></span>
<span class="progress-ongoing">Deploying…</span>
<span class="progress-done">Done!</span>
</pre>
</section>

<section class="alt">
  <h2>Optimized for speed</h2>
  <p>Average deploy time with Upstatic is only 3 seconds when using concurrent file uploads. Upstatic also <a href="/usage/">keeps&nbsp;track</a> of&nbsp;all your changes and deploys only the&nbsp;files that have&nbsp;changed.</p>
